:::summary
The New Testament is the fulfillment of everything the Old Testament promised — a collection of 27 books, written in Greek within a generation of the resurrection of Jesus Christ, that proclaim the good news of God's redemption of humanity through his Son. From the four Gospels to Paul's letters to the Apocalypse of John, the New Testament is the living heart of the Christian faith, the most influential set of documents in human history, and the testimony of eyewitnesses and their associates to the most important events ever recorded.
:::

